 of good pairs, as each previous occurrence can form a good pair with the current number. Then, it increments the count of the current number in the dictionary. This approach ensures that each pair is counted exactly once and runs in O(n) time complexity, where n is the length of the input list.", "estimated_date": 1594512000000}